HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 572
By Hale
A RESOLUTION to recognize Allyson Trapp on the occasion of
her being named the 2024–2025 Smithville
Elementary School Teacher of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should specially recognize those outstanding teachers
who have devoted their careers to providing the highest-quality education for Tennessee's
students; and
WHEREAS, Allyson Trapp is one such estimable educator, who has distinguished
herself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Trapp has been selected as the Smithville Elementary School Teacher
of the Year, an honor most befitting her outstanding tenure as a first-grade teacher, as it
recognizes the positive influence she has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, Allyson Trapp is an extremely talented and compassionate educator who
has worked assiduously to motivate her students to reach their full potential, both as scholars
and as citizens; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Trapp serves as an inspiration to her colleagues and students alike,
and her friendship and counsel are highly valued by those who are fortunate to know her; and
WHEREAS, Allyson Trapp truly epitomizes the dedicated teacher who is wholly
committed to the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and she should be
specially recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Allyson Trapp on being chosen as the 2024–
2025 Smithville Elementary School Teacher of the Year, commend her exceptional service to
